<subSubSection id="B224BD1AEBF48676F33D96EA8849D06F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="BAE09542AFC9429C05494C3157EBA907" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D106A988C1300B837C88138DE48CDFC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="1DEC60AB37F0F7663247821A5E19DB9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wright</emphasis>
3094
<potBibRef id="7249F30D410CF4325EBBC9FC0123D954">
, 
<emphasis id="2193E38DD458EC8076CCDBAA1AAE2142" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shafer</emphasis>
2607
</potBibRef>
from Camaguey and sine data from Bahamas (K) have 3-5 lobed leaves. Other specimens have entire leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE47A3AA9BF82E64791F0FC1A39ACFC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="A8B0200DCEDD2BD6C39D08583F96EB94" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beyeriana">
<emphasis id="B6352852D0A1F864AE32F73A42BE5F97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea beyeriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type. We believe it is an entire-leaved form of 
<taxonomicName id="87C84C4C878B64A0062721FDE3324636" authority="Griseb." authorityName="Griseb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microdactyla">
<emphasis id="D6C5EE81083D55DA473B3F6B945FC7A5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. microdactyla</emphasis>
Griseb.
</taxonomicName>
, based on the leaf shape and the reddish sepals. Urban (1925: 425) suggested an affinity with 
<taxonomicName id="4A63464267D875D79A202CC9C6F1655D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuchsioides">
<emphasis id="AF8A5BDC8091D3887343A712EA11DD1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea fuchsioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is not unlike the type of 
<taxonomicName id="6BAD2583158647C68427D4D781D0AA5A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fuchsioides" variety="glabra">
<emphasis id="2E5228000E3CD33ED1305CF39A94BDC0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. fuchsioides</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="C0E8407D90B021EC33A728BBCA0A75CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is an even better match for 
<emphasis id="C8879625922184A3F732D4DC870F2B23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wright</emphasis>
3102, the type of 
<taxonomicName id="68D7FA1C40D7C3665E13040F3CE8931D" authority="House." authorityName="House." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Exogonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="microdactylum" variety="integrifolium">
<emphasis id="FE18B494DFA14D2BF296A6635295F758" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Exogonium microdactylum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="41B07F0E72E6AB2178428E1649A24311" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">integrifolium</emphasis>
House.
</taxonomicName>
(Wood and Scotland 2017c).
</paragraph>
